      What is logos images?
      Logos are images, texts, shapes, or a combination of the three that depict the name and purpose of a business to put it simply. However, a logo can and should be more than a symbol of identification. If designed well, it also tells a company's story, by conveying your brand message.

      What is a JPEG logo?
      JPEGs (also known as JPG files) are a standard logo file format for digital use. Clients and developers often use JPEG files. While JPEGs have a slightly lower resolution than PNG files, JPEG images load faster on websites. JPEG files may have an RGB or CMYK color profile.06-Oct-2021

      What is a brand logo?
      A logo is a graphic device that identifies a brand. Sometimes it's referred to as a trademark. Your logo can consist of a symbol and a typographic wordmark, or even just a typographic wordmark on its own in some cases. Because the logo identifies your brand, it's an incredibly important strategic tool.
